The energy values of acridine yellow adsorption on silica, titania–silica, and titania surfaces were found according to Hess law from the total energy values for calculated models as follows:ΔEads=Etotalads.comp.-(Etotalsurface+EtotalAY).\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
